<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 30-SI AND 30-SI/TR SERIES - REPAIR PROCEDURES - STATOR CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>STATOR CHECK</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>(Omit for overcharged battery.)</title>
            <para>Most stators are delta wound and only a check for grounds can be made with an ohmmeter. Connect from
                either lead to the frame (Step 4,
                <hotlnk document="s08016_11.xml" xrefid="f0801613">Figure 13</hotlnk>). The reading should be infinite.
                If not, replace the stator. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08016_HL0801608.xml" xrefid="hl0801608">DISASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>If the regulator checks good and if the generator fails to supply rated output, replace the stator if
                it is badly discolored.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
